IN 'CODE BREAKER'; YOU MUST GUESS AFOURDIGIT CODE.  EACH DIGIT MAYRANGE ROM   1-9 (NO ZEROES); ANDTHERE WILL BE NO   DUPLICATE DIGITS.ENTER A SERIES OF GUESSES.  AFTEREACH  GUESS; YOU'LL BE TOLD HOW MANYDIGITS   IN YOUR GUESS ARE ALSO INTHE CODE.     'D' WILL BE THE NUMBEROF DIGITS IN THECODE THAT ARE IN THE WRONG POSITION.'P' WILL BE THE NUMBER OF DIGITS INTHE CODE THAT ARE IN THE RIGHTPOSITION.YOU MAY SUBMIT A GUESS WITHDUPLICATE   DIGITS.  IF YOU DO SO;AND ONE OF THE   DUPLICATED DIGITSIS ALSO IN THE CODE;  EACH DUPLICATEWILL BE COUNTED IN 'D'   AND/OR 'P';DESPITE THAT IT ONLY APPEARSONCE INTHE CODE.